headline: Nvidia stock soared 35,000% over the past decade — but it's not the only top chip stock for the future
summary: Wall Street still loves Nvidia and Broadcom, but analysts say lesser-known names may offer just as much upside.

headline: OpenLight Raises $34M Series A to Scale Next-Gen Integrated Photonics for AI Data Centers
summary: OpenLight, a leader in custom Photonic Application-Specific Integrated Circuit (PASIC) chip design and manufacturing based on heterogeneous integration, today announced the close of its oversubscribed $34M Series A. The round is co-led by Xora Innovation and Capricorn Investment Group. Other participants include Mayfield; Juniper Networks, now part of HPE; Lam Capital, the corporate venture arm of Lam Research Corporation; New Legacy Ventures; and K2 Access.
